## [Diagonal difference - HackerRank solution in Python and c++](https://github.com/codePerfectPlus/competitive-programming-solution/tree/master/HackerRank/Problem%20Solving)

> Problem Statement: Given a square matrix, calculate the absolute difference between the sums of its diagonals.

```cpp
int diagonalDifference(vector<vector<int>> arr) {

    int s1 = 0;
    int s2 = 0;
    int n = arr.size();

    for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {        
        s1 += arr[i][i];
        s2 += arr[i][n-i-1];
    }
    return abs(s1 - s2); 
}
```

```python
def diagonalDifference(arr):
    # Write your code here
    d1 = sum(arr[i][i] for i in range(n))
    d2 = sum(arr[i][n-i-1] for i in range(n))
    return abs(d1 - d2)
```

